// ============================================================================
//  CLUB_STATION.cpp
//  Smart Beverage Antenna Selector — CLUBHOUSE STATION (CLUB / Authority)
//  ----------------------------------------------------------------------
//  Target: ESP32 + TFT_eSPI touchscreen display + KY-040 rotary encoder
//
//  Role
//   - Authoritative controller and single source of truth for antenna state.
//   - Accepts selection requests from:
//       (1) local rotary encoder UI, and
//       (2) MQTT commands from REMOTE panels.
//   - Executes physical switching only on committed selections.
//   - Publishes authoritative antenna state as a retained MQTT message.
//
//  Runtime Model
//   - Encoder PREVIEW → COMMIT model:
//       • Rotation updates a preview antenna (UI highlight only).
//       • When rotation stops for PREVIEW_SETTLE_MS, preview is committed.
//       • Hardware switching is executed once per commit.
//       • Retained state is published after commit.
//   - Map mode:
//       • First encoder detent exits map view (no selection, no MQTT traffic).
//
//  Connectivity & Services
//   - WiFi provisioning via HB9IIUPortal (AP name: HB9IIUPortal / beverage).
//   - Secure MQTT via HiveMQ Cloud over TLS (port 8883).
//   - ElegantOTA firmware updates served via WebServer (port 80).
//   - SNTP time sync (UTC + local TZ for display).
//
//  MQTT Topics (CLUB role)
//   - SUBSCRIBE: antenna/cmd        (selection requests from remotes)
//   - PUBLISH  : antenna/state      (authoritative retained state)
//   - PUBLISH  : antenna/heartbeat  (defined; optional / future use)
//
//  Design Guarantees
//   - Deterministic state: no speculative reporting.
//   - Hardware actions are edge-triggered on commit only (no relay/DTMF chatter).
//   - REMOTE presence is inferred from received user commands only.
//
//  Author : Daniel / HB9IIU
//  Date   : 2025-12-20
//  Changes to apply om REMOTE
//
// ============================================================================

